She allowed Planet, the winning boat, 23 minutes 59 seconds in a four-and-a-half-mile race, and was all but lapped with her when the little Southern flier crossed the finish line.

abstract: BUFFALO, Feb, 7. -- A reconciliation has been brought about between Attorney General William S. Jackson and his wife. abstract: OMAHA, Feb. 7. -- Count John A. Creighton died at his home here early to-day. He was born in Licking County, Ohio, Oct. 15, 1831. abstract: ANNAPOLIS, Md., Feb. 22. -The fencing team of Columbia lost to the Midshipmen here this afternoon by a score of 4 to 5 in an interesting competition. abstract: Between four and five inches of snow descended upon the city yesterday and then toward 8:30 o'clock it began to rain. abstract: Another novelty was brought forward last night at the Manhattan Opera House in the shape of Verdi's "Ballo in Maschera," a work, which, though it has been sung spasmodically in recent years at the Broadway house, has not been sufficiently obtruded on the public to make it in any way familiar to the majority of operagoers.

abstract: District Attorney Jerome spent all of yesterday hewing close to the line he has mapped out for bringing an insanity commission into the trial of Harry K. Thaw for the murder of Stanford White. He endeavored to wring from Dr. Britton D. Evans, one of the alienists for the defense, his opinion as to the present condition of the defendant's mind, and did get from him the admission that he had an opinion.

abstract: BOSTON, Feb. 27. -- The expected report of a special Committee on Athletics at Harvard University was submitted by President Eliot to-day to the Board of Overseers of the institution.
